  <html:table
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  
  
  <html:tr>
    
  <html:th>Fluid Binding</html:th>

    
  <html:th>Default</html:th>

    
  <html:th>Meaning</html:th>

  </html:tr>

  
  <html:tr>
    
  <html:td><fr:code><![CDATA[\transclude/]]>title</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td><fr:em>(none)</fr:em></html:td>

    
  <html:td>To override the tree's title during transclusion.</html:td>

  </html:tr>

  
  <html:tr>
    
  <html:td><fr:code><![CDATA[\transclude/]]>toc</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td><fr:code>true</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td>Show the tree in the table of contents.</html:td>

  </html:tr>

  
  <html:tr>
    
  <html:td><fr:code><![CDATA[\transclude/]]>expanded</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td><fr:code>true</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td>Whether the tree is expanded or not.</html:td>

  </html:tr>

  
  <html:tr>
    
  <html:td><fr:code><![CDATA[\transclude/]]>heading</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td><fr:code>true</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td>If set to <fr:code>false</fr:code>, the tree's contents will be inlined.</html:td>

  </html:tr>

  
  <html:tr>
    
  <html:td><fr:code><![CDATA[\transclude/]]>metadata</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td><fr:code>false</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td>Show in a tree's heading.</html:td>

  </html:tr>

  
  <html:tr>
    
  <html:td><fr:code><![CDATA[\transclude/]]>numbered</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td><fr:code>true</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td>Whether the tree is displayed with a number or not, transitively on subtrees.</html:td>

  </html:tr>

</html:table>
<fr:p>It is possible to achieve undesirable results by combining these options in undesirable ways; it is up to you to use them correctly.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter><fr:tree
